    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-21T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/887: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-21T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 21, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Embassy’s 160, November 19, 5 p.m.<note n="51" xml:id="d628fn51">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from Yunnanfu: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“November 20, 4 p.m. Referring to the Embassy’s telegram November 9, 11
                            a.m. to Canton.</p>
                        <p>Yunnan having its own monetary system independent of the Central
                            Government, this province is not affected by the nationalization of
                            silver and there has been little comment engendered thereby. Yunnan
                            silver currency continues to circulate”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
